text: The Birdsville Developmental Road (State Route 14) is a mostly unsealed road in south-west Queensland that branches off the Diamantina Developmental Road at a point west of Windorah and runs to Birdsville.Queensland Government - Department of Transport and Main Roads - Maps Its length is . The road crosses a major channel of the Diamantina River just prior to reaching Birdsville. ==See also== * Highways in Australia * List of highways in Queensland ==References== Category:Roads in Queensland
title: Birdsville Developmental Road
